Identity & Access Management Group(Global Service)

Groups only contains users not other groups.
User can belongs to multiple groups
Users or Group can be assigned JSON documents called policies

Step 1 — Navigate to IAM:
      Go to AWS Console → Search for IAM(IAM is a Global Service — it applies across all AWS regions)
      In the left panel, click Users → Click "Create User"
Step 2 — Set User Details:
      Enter a User Name
      Check "Provide user access to the AWS Management Console"
      Under Select Console Access → Select "I want to create an IAM User" radio button → Click Next
Step 3 — Set Password:
      Choose "Custom Password" and enter your desired password
      Uncheck "Users must create a new password at next sign-in"(This means the user will NOT be prompted to change the password on next login)
      Click Next
Step 4 — Create a User Group:
      Click "Create Group"
      Enter Group Name: admin
      Search and attach the policy: AdministratorAccess
      Click "Create User Group"
      Select the newly created admin group → Click Next
Step 5 — Review and Create:
      Review all the details
      Click "Create User"
      ⚠️ Download or copy the Console sign-in URL and password before closing
Step 6 — Set Account Alias:
      In the left panel, click on Dashboard
      Under AWS Account section, find "Account Alias"
      Click "Create" or "Edit" → Enter your custom alias name
      Click "Save changes"
      💡 The Account Alias replaces the default AWS Account ID in the sign-in URL:
https://your-alias.signin.aws.amazon.com/console
